# anarchy-client environment template
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and edit. `.env` is gitignored so per-host
# values stay out of source control. Only variables prefixed with
# `VITE_` are exposed to client code (Vite enforces this).
#
# WebSocket endpoint the client connects to. When unset, the client
# falls back to `ws://localhost:8080/ws` (local dev against a server
# started via `cargo run` in the sibling repo).
#
# To share a build through a Cloudflare quick-tunnel:
#   1. Run the server locally on :8080 (plaintext; tunnel handles TLS).
#   2. `cloudflared tunnel --url http://localhost:8080` and copy the
#      generated `https://<name>.trycloudflare.com/` hostname.
#   3. Set the matching `wss://` WebSocket URL here, e.g.:
#        VITE_WS_URL=wss://my-tunnel-name.trycloudflare.com/ws
#   4. `npm run build` (or restart `npm run dev`) — Vite inlines the
#      value at build/serve time.
#
# Direct TLS (server bound with --tls-cert / --tls-key, no tunnel):
#   VITE_WS_URL=wss://my-host.example.com:8080/ws
#
# Runtime overrides (no rebuild required):
#   - `?ws=ws://...`           full URL, wins over everything else.
#   - `?server-port=NNNN`      synthesises ws://localhost:NNNN/ws (used
#                              by the player-accounts e2e spec).
#VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8080/ws
